Usage: read_twf [-help] [<filenames>] [-cell <string>] [-prefix <string>]
                [-quiet] [-reset] [-scope <string>] [-skipconst] [-skiptw]
                [-strip_prefix <string>] [-total_load_only] [-verbose]
                [-view <string>]

-help                           # Prints out the command usage
<filenames>                     # Specifies the names of the timing window
                                # files (string, optional)
-cell <string>                  # Specifies master cell for the timing window
                                # file (string, optional)
-prefix <string>                # Adds a prefix to the net or pin name
                                # (string, optional)
-quiet                          # Skips infor and warning messages
                                # (bool, optional)
-reset                          # Clears the previously read TWF files
                                # (bool, optional)
-scope <string>                 # Specifies the scope for the given
                                # hierarchical timing window file
                                # (string, optional)
-skipconst                      # Skips constant processing (bool, optional)
-skiptw                         # Skips timing windows processing
                                # (bool, optional)
-strip_prefix <string>          # Removes hierarchical path name
                                # (string, optional)
-total_load_only                # If only read TOTAL_LOAD from Twf
                                # (bool, optional)
-verbose                        # Generates a detail report (bool, optional)
-view <string>                  # Specifies the view for the timing window file
                                # (string, optional)